0.body: Ankoku is a lightweight embeddable scripting language written in Rust. The main inspirations are JavaScript, Rust, and Java-style OOP. If you know JavaScript, Ankoku should be easy to pick up.
0.title: Introduction

10.body: Functions are instances of the Function class, which is an FFI class and private. They expose a few methods, generally for making more functions.

11.body: Call this function with the specified arguments. Implemented in the VM.

12.body:
Bind this function with a starting number of parameters. Most commonly used to bind this in Object.new. Example implementation: fn Function.bind(this, ...arguments) { return fn(...args) { return this.call(arguments.concat(args)); }
}
